docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Aug. 28 -- As Congress headed into the fourth, and possibly final, week of its pre-election session, Senate and House leaders prepared today to deal with foreign aid, a higher minimum wage and medical care for the aged.

headline.main: SENATE TO BALLOT TODAY ON A PLAN FOR CARE OF AGED; Congress, Entering Fourth Week, Faces Battles on Aid and Wage Bills DEMOCRATS UNDER FIRE Javits Says Majority Has Achieved Little -- Douglas Deplores 'Coalition' SENATE WILL VOTE ON CARE FOR AGED
